  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05/D3 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The package embeds a subtle W-AR-05 weakener: the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link, while the supporting narrative references a well-regarded experimental dataset whose operating conditions (ventricular-assist duty cycle, 4–6 L/min at 3500–5000 RPM) overlap substantially with the CPB envelope but differ on the clinically decisive parameter — blood priming volume and recirculation fraction — making the comparator inappropriate for the declared COU without disclosing that mismatch.",
