      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/no-comparator",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary hemolysis QoI validation — relative hemolysis index",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) values were computed across five operating points (2.5 L/min at 2800 RPM; 3.5 L/min at 3200 RPM; 4.5 L/min at 3600 RPM; 5.0 L/min at 3800 RPM; 6.0 L/min at 4200 RPM) representing the full CPB duty envelope. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen–Wurzinger coefficients) was applied to Lagrangian particle trajectories extracted from converged RANS solutions. Predicted RHI values ranged from 0.61 to 0.94 across the five points, with worst-case identified at 2.5 L/min / 2800 RPM, consistent with high-shear recirculation zones observed in the impeller-volute gap. Mesh independence was confirmed at 8.2 M cells (GCI < 1.2%). The validation narrative notes strong agreement with published experimental hemolysis characterisation data for a geometrically similar centrifugal pump platform, and the assessment team considers the model adequately validated for rank-ordering hemolysis severity across operating conditions. No statistically significant bias was detected in the QoI distribution. The validation is rated as meeting the required level for MRL 2 under the Output comparison factor.",
      "validationScore": 3,
      "validationMethod": "Comparison of CFD-predicted RHI against published experimental hemolysis data for a centrifugal pump platform characterised under ventricular-assist device duty conditions"
