      "rationale": "The experimental dataset referenced for hemolysis validation (Leverett et al. power-law basis; Giersiepen–Wurzinger coefficients derived from Couette-flow experiments) is well-documented in the open literature. Fluid properties (bovine blood, 37°C, Hct 35%) are reported. The assessment team notes that the primary comparator was characterised under ventricular-assist device (VAD) recirculation conditions; the CPB circuit differs in priming volume and recirculation fraction, but the team considers the overlap in shear-stress exposure history sufficient for Gradation 2 purposes."
