      "rationale": "RHI is the standard industry metric for comparative hemolysis assessment in blood-contacting devices (ISO 10993-4, ASTM F1841). Its use as a rank-ordering QoI for worst-case identification under dimensional variation is consistent with the COU. The model outputs RHI directly from integrated shear-exposure along particle trajectories, providing a single scalar per operating point suitable for the five-point comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
