      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must address the same geometry class, flow regime, and hemolysis mechanism as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the same geometry as the COU device. Flow regimes (turbulent, Re ~ 10^4–10^5) and hemolysis mechanism (sub-lethal shear stress accumulation) are consistent. The assessment team considers the validation activities sufficiently relevant, noting that the experimental comparator was obtained under VAD rather than CPB circuit conditions; however, pump-internal fluid mechanics are considered geometry-dominated at these Reynolds numbers, and circuit-level differences are judged secondary."
    },
