      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its established performance for separated flows in rotating machinery (Menter 1994; multiple FDA benchmark studies). The Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the de facto standard for CFD hemolysis prediction in blood pumps and is accepted by FDA guidance. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged but considered acceptable for rank-ordering at MRL 2."
