    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for MRL 2. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions across the five-point CPB duty envelope. The relative hemolysis index predictions are conservative (positive bias) with respect to the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The assessment team acknowledges that the primary experimental comparator was characterised under VAD circuit conditions rather than CPB circuit conditions, but considers this difference secondary to pump-internal fluid mechanics for the purpose of rank-ordering hemolysis severity. No unresolved credibility gaps were identified.",
